a: You got the map of the Looseleaf Kingdom.+
It is faded and unreadable. However, if you rise to the peak of an ink fountain and look around at your surroundings, you can fill in what was lost.+
Even then, [0]rooms you have yet to visit will appear more faded[/]. You can use this to keep track of where you've been.+
This map can be accessed through a button on the pause menu, or more quickly by simply pressing M.+
Wonderful. You have returned to your point of origin, now having acquired additional abilities. The Defaced Deity will be no match.+
However, it might have been easier to return here through the fountains instead.+
You see, if you [0]delve deep into the crevasse[/], you can travel through the ink tunnels to [0]any fountain[/] you've previously visited.+
I hope this is helpful. If anything is troubling you, do not hesitate to ask my associate the Eraser.+
Hmm. So you *can* follow directions.=
Would've been nice if you had done that when I was trying to take over the world, but whatever.=
By the way, d'you nab that [0]map[/] down there? In a kingdom this big, I'm sure it'll come in handy.=
And if you ever find that your map isn't helpful enough, just ask me for help whenever. I'll be hanging out in your [0]pause menu[/].=
As much as I hate this arrangement, I promise I'll hold up my end as long as you promise to beat up that weird deity thing.=
Well, this is a fine mess you've gotten us into. The entrance to the ruins was sealed for, what, a thousand years?=
Then you come along and seal it up again, trapping us in here for who knows how long...=
Hopefully there's something around here we can use to find an exit.=
Oh, and don't forget your map either! Can you check if there's an ink fountain nearby?=
Oh hey, you're stuck now. That's kinda funny.=
You remember that thing about [0]pressing R[/] or whatever, right?=
...You seem stuck.+
Want some advice?+
Don't think of this as "level 2"... but rather, one of many paths to explore.+
You'll find more helpful things elsewhere.+
Hey! The heck are you doing back here again? D'you die or something? That's funny.=
Still, I'd rather not have to watch you go all the way back to where you died, so...=
Wait, I just remembered. Dying sends you back to the last ink fountain, but your "progress" is still "saved", whatever that means.=
So, any [0]shortcuts[/] you opened up... Those would still be open, wouldn't they?=
Those could speed things up quite a bit.=
Whoa, can't help but notice you're running a little low on ink there.=
Or... wait, maybe not. A white ring just appeared around your ink meter... Could that be your [0]backup ink[/]?=
You can press C to transfer backup ink (as long as you have some) into your main ink (as long as there's room).+
Consider doing this often, as you perish if your ink drops to 0 percent.+

I notice you're standing in front of me. What is it?
Ah, it's you. I assume you'd like me to tell you what I've discovered?
Nothing to tell, I'm afraid. This is just where I come to rest during my travels. For somewhere so safe from the prowling ink creatures, it's surprisingly easy to get to.
Why don't I rest in the town...? Well, the lava moat for one. Besides, the quiet life isn't for me.
I'd best be off soon, but I suppose we could chat while we're here.

Vq: How many discoveries have I found?

a: Your face... it wears the determined expression of a dedicated explorer, but lacks the scars and weariness of an experienced one.
My name? That doesn't matter. What matters is you. Something tells me you are unfamiliar with the history of the Looseleaf Kingdom, is this correct?
I consider myself something of a historian. I've scoured the kingdom in an attempt to piece together the extensive history, most of which has been lost to time.
This monument seems to be a memorial to the lives that were lost during the [0]First Tragedy[/]. The text is written in an ancient script I cannot decipher...
Would you like to hear about the First Tragedy?
Which discovery would you like me to discuss?
Very well. I'll soon be on my way. If you change your mind, we can discuss this matter anytime.
A millenium ago, the Great Sages were tragically betrayed by one of their own.
In a ploy for world domination, [0]the Ruler[/] planned to flood the Looseleaf Kingdom with ink he had corrupted...
And anyone who touched the ink would be overwritten, forced to act upon the Ruler's will.
He left the birthplace of the sages in ruin in an event that came to be known as "the First Tragedy".
The Sages created a seal around the kingdom's capital, preventing the ink from spreading further... for a time.
Though the seal remains intact, and the ink held within long since dried out... somehow, the corruption has returned.
You and I... we are among the few fortunate enough to remain unaffected.
Rumor has it that the Ruler still has loyal followers, determined to free him from his prison and unleash what has been foretold as "the Final Tragedy".
They call themselves the Order of the Ruler, but their hideout remains shrouded in secrecy. Could they be the ones behind all of this?
In truth, it's been a long time since I've been asked about my feelings... Even longer since I've tried to put them into words.
I like to keep to myself and take life as it comes. No need to ponder my part in it all.
You seem like the quiet type yourself... I assume you understand.
It's not an easy life, but I wouldn't trade it for anything.
At this point, you should be about as familiar with the life of an explorer as I.
You know how it is. Aching bones. Constant itchiness. Scrapes all over. A fatigue that blankets your vision like mist.
And, underneath it all, the heart-pounding thrill of discovery, the feeling of being truly and utterly alive. A sensation few will ever experience.
We're lucky, you and I.

OPERAND2: How many discoveries have I found?

a: By my estimation, there are 9 major historical discoveries to be found across the kingdom.
aM=
You have been graced with the power of ink.+
[0]Click and drag the mouse[/] to draw lines that you can walk on. This depletes your ink, so don't rely on this power too much!+
If you wish to erase your lines, [0]press R[/]. This will also send you back to where you entered a room, so remember this in case you get stuck.+
To check and remap your controls, select "Controls" on the pause menu (press P).+
^Well, well, well. If it isn't you again.=
Looks like you've changed since we've last met... Then again, that's true for both of us, isn't it?=
Huh? You don't remember your formerly-mortal enemy [0]The Eraser[/]?! I guess it *has* been a while...=
Look, I realize we've had our squabbles in the past, what with me trying to take over the world, and you defeating me...=
But what we're up against now is on another level. I hate to suggest it, but... we'll have to work together on this one.=
Anyway, I couldn't help but notice you just acquired the power of corrupted ink. What are you, immune to it or something?=
If so, you're our best bet at stopping this once and for all... with my guidance, of course.=
>Heh heh... Your life is in my hands once again. What should I tell you to do first...?=
So you fell down here from some kind of [0]inky fountain[/], right? Yeah, you should probably get back up there.=
You'll lose some ink along the way, but those things spew out more than enough to make up the difference, so don't worry about it.=
I won't fault you for taking the time to explore first, though. You never know what cool junk you might find around here.=
You have been graced with the power of the Drawn Dagger.+
[0]Press Z to draw your weapon[/], which damages enemies and other destructible objects if touched.+
Any enemies you defeat will give you extra ink to fill your backup meter.+
Oh, that's right... You have not been informed about your backup ink, have you?+
No matter. I'm sure the Eraser will explain this concept as soon as your ink drops below 40 percent.+
You have been graced with the power of white ink.+
With this, you can draw tunnels through walls, but only in certain areas.+
If your [0]pen cursor starts to glow[/], that means there is a place to use white ink within that room. Keep this in mind the next time you encounter a dead end.+
Within such walls, your pen will automatically switch to using white ink.+
Oh hey, new ability. You're really rackin' those up, huh?=
You can probably use this somewhere... Check the map for areas of the ruins you haven't visited yet.=
Unvisited rooms are more faded, remember?=
Wait, you haven't visited the ink fountain, so this entire area isn't on your map at all yet. Oh well, it's pretty close. You'll probably find it.=
After all this time, the seal to the Inkwell Ruins has been broken! Who did this? How is such a thing even possible?!
Regardless, I'm glad I finally got to explore that place I've been so curious about. Though, I've got to say... it was a bit underwhelming, honestly.
I've heard so many cool legends about it, but I guess a lot of that stuff didn't survive the thousand years. I guess that's to be expected.
Like, there's this one legend about a mechanical beast created to destroy the corrupted ink, but I haven't found anything of the sort.
No treasure either, though I imagine some of these ancient pebbles could be sold to a museum for a decent price.
In the Age of the Sages, the [0]Inkwell Ruins[/] were the kingdom's bustling capital.
The legends tell of its civilization wielding technology beyond our comprehension...
And even in the millenium since the civilization's fall, we have yet to reach that level of advancement.
Mostly because, ever since the First Tragedy, none have been able to make it past the entrance...
As such, the city's ancient secrets were left behind, becoming nothing more than fables passed down to each generation.
It's a shame, really. I've always wanted to see what treasures and secrets await inside.
[0]Tempera Town[/] is just ahead! Please be careful of the lava moat around the town.
Unless you're one of those gross ink creatures, in which case, don't.
You enjoyin' that artifact I gave you? Dunno what it's for, but it seems powerful.
Thanks, pal. I like things a lot better on this side of the moat.
To repay your kindness, lessee, I got one of these here [0]artifacts[/]... you got any use for something like that?
(You got a [0]Mark of Recovery[/].)
So are you going to draw a path this week, or should I wait until my birthday? Hurry up already!
You call that a path?! *You* might be some kind of acrobat, but *I* can't get across with that!
Sweet, my sincerest thanks. Now off to that town I've forgotten the name of after two years.
So, what's up? You talked to anyone in the town about me?

Zq: I'll help you cross the moat.

a: I saw you go over there and talk to some guy, but you didn't say anything? What's the darn holdup?!
So you're just gonna respond with awkward silence, huh? Sure, go on and pretend I never asked a simple question.
That's swell. So you said you had, uh, magic ink or whatever, right?
That's swell. So, uh, maybe this is a bit presumptuous, but... you were lying about the walking through lava thing, weren't you?
Yeah, I figured. You must have some kind of, uh, magical drawing powers or something, like in the legends.
That's swell. But, uh, you never told me how you got across...
I assume you must have some kind of, uh, magical drawing powers, right? Like in the legends?
So could you, like, create some kind of path for me to walk across? That would be great.
Come to visit Tempera Town? Sorry, pal, you ain't allowed entry unless you can cross this moat.
Tempera Town is the last bit of structured civilization after the incident, and this lava right here is all that sits between it and those ink monsters.
So why am I here, you ask?
Well... I was in charge of creating the moat, and I ended up getting stuck on the wrong side.
I've been waiting here for about two years for someone to notice and come back for me.
...Any day now.
So, uh, where does one find magic ink?
Is it the sorta thing you can find at a grocery store, or do you have to perform sacred rituals to summon otherworldly sorcery, or what?
\\...What do you mean the power would collapse my mind such that I'd be driven to a state of insanity fueled by unending torment?
Maybe I'll just build a bridge.
Hmm... if I want to learn to walk through lava, maybe I should start in the volcanoes of Fliptanaria.
Kind of ease into it, you know? Start with third-degree burns, work my way up to fourth, fifth... and so forth.
What are you still doing here? Go away.
You've gotten across the moat? What's your secret?!
...Huh. And I don't suppose powers like those would be, uh, easy to come by, would they?
I mean, if you could, like, somehow share some of your power, with me... that'd be swell.
...No, no, I understand. But, uh, while you were over there...
Did you at least put in a good word for me? Remind anyone that I exist?
...Ah. Well, if you ever get the chance... I'd appreciate it.
You jumped into a pool of molten lava made of the most painful red ink...
And you just kinda... walked through it? That answer... honestly just raises more questions.
Like... How? Why? \What? Who?\ \\WHEN? WHERE?!
Oh, no, it's fine, you don't have to answer. Just, uh, while you were over there...
Did you at least put in a good word for me? Remind anyone that I exist?
...Ah. Well, if you ever get the chance... I'd appreciate it.
Ouch. That's cold.
All right, then. Keep your secrets.
...Any day now.
Oh, thank goodness. The moat creator made it back safely. I've been so worried.
Soon I'll give him my immense apologies for leaving him behind... soon. I'm still working up the courage...
Hello again. Is there something you'd like to discuss?
The moat creator, you say? He's still out there?
My goodness, how awful of me, I never checked. It's been too dangerous to set foot outside the town and I... I'm afraid I assumed the worst. I'm so sorry.
What can I do? The moat is intentionally made too wide to cross. But, then again...
You crossed it, didn't you? I don't know how, but you're here, so you must have. If you don't mind, could you... help him somehow?
I'm so terribly sorry there's not more I can do. Truly, I feel horrible about all of this.
Hello again. Would you like to listen once more to the story of our town?
Hello again. Would you like to listen to the story of our town? I assure you, it is a short one, and I rarely get to speak to new visitors...
Welcome to Tempera Town. It's not much, but I hope you can make yourself at home regardless.
We don't get many visitors these days, so please, stay as long as you like. We have plenty of food and resources stored here, we're at little risk of running out.
Would you like to hear the story of our town?
Well, as I'm sure you know, the corrupted ink started spreading about two years ago. Things really haven't been the same since then...
With most civilization in ruin, we hurried to protect what was left... which, at the time, was merely this small village.
We put a moat of lava around the town to defend ourselves from the ink monsters, and we've managed to eke out a relatively peaceful existence here.
Thanks to the moat and the natural protection from the foliage surrounding us, this is one of the few areas in the kingdom safe from the corruption.
I sincerely hope it's to your liking.
Ah, fair enough. You've already heard it, after all.
Ah. Some other time, perhaps.
Hey, welcome back to my shop!
Hmm... can I really call it a shop if I've got nothing to sell...?
Would you look at that, a new customer! This here is my shop. Come to buy something?
After the corruption started taking over, I started giving out almost all of my stock for free to help the survivors.
But you're in luck, because I just so happen to have one last item in stock. And it's quite the doozy, let me tell you.
This is what's known as an [0]artifact[/], a slip of paper with great power.
This one here is called "[0]Coat of Mail[/]", and it increases your defense so you won't lose as much ink if you get hurt.
Apparently you can equip artifacts by... "pressing P and clicking manage artifacts"? I don't know... I'm sure there's someone nearby who could explain it better than I could.
I'll give it to you for free. Not like money's got much value these days.
What is it? Don't tell me you want to hear the story again.
My mumbling? I assure you, it's nothing. Just a bad habit, I suppose.
Let's just leave it at that, shall we?
Very well. As I've said, I was a scientist at Ballpoint Base, the lab in Deepenfoul...
Really? If you really want to know, well... I suppose it's not much of a secret anyhow.
You see, I... was a scientist at Ballpoint Base, the lab in Deepenfoul...
We were continuing the work of the Sages after their departure. They had sealed away the corrupted ink long ago, but we knew this approach was fallible.
If the containment was breached, the world as we know it could end. And, well... it did. But I'm getting ahead of myself.
With the help of my colleagues, I was able to synthesize a small amount of pure ink to counteract the alteration...
The plan was to use this pure ink to destroy the corrupted ink once and for all, eliminating the risk of further corruption.
All we needed to do was create more pure ink. A complicated procedure it may have been, but a world-saving one.
It was a good plan, and we were mere weeks away from the success we had been working toward for years. The world would be safe at last.
However, it seems irony decided to mock us, for that was exactly when the seal was breached and the corruption began to spread once more.
I was foolish. I knew what the corrupted ink was capable of, I knew the risk of it spreading throughout the kingdom and infecting the populace...
And yet I, being the dimwitted optimist that I was, didn't care. Not as much as I should have. I only worked eight hours a day, took weekends off...
It was unlikely for the seal to break, I told myself. The chances were a mere fraction of a fraction of a percent. And yet, here we are.
If I had only worked harder, if only I had spent more time preparing the antidote...
Perhaps the world wouldn't lay in ruin. Perhaps I could have prevented the loss of hundreds. Perhaps I wouldn't have to live each day with... such guilt.
The ink has spread too far now. Even going through with the plan would accomplish nothing.
I know I shouldn't feel responsible... I couldn't have known when this tragedy would occur. But I feel at fault nonetheless.
I know I should give up hope, but there's a small part of me that thinks something can be done.
I studied the corrupted ink, I know better than anyone how unstoppable it is. And yet, I cannot accept it.
There's so much we don't know about it. Some weakness that has yet to be discovered, perhaps.
I... almost wish I had no hope. It's easier that way, knowing that nothing can be done...
But I see something in you. Potential, perhaps? It's not like me to ignore the logic of things, but...
Somehow, I feel like you can change this. Go forth, and do what I failed to do.
I'm sorry, it seems I have rambled quite a bit. That must have been tiresome. You may leave.
Very well.
>(You could have stopped this, it's your fault everyone's...)
Ah, a newcomer. I apologize, I do tend to mumble to myself on occasion. Pay no mind to it. It's a pleasure to meet you.
Be careful, okay?
We don't get many visitors here. It seemed like everyone had been... well, except you. How did you survive?
Your courage... your perseverance... it reminds me of my son.
You can stay here, you know. The world is dangerous, but this town... it's safe. You never have to leave.
Just, whatever you do... be careful, okay?
JEFFREY! You're alive!
...Oh... I'm sorry.
I must've mistaken you for... someone else.
Dude. You want to, like, like, dude, talk about, like, something, dude?

Zq: Tell me more about the kingdom regions.

a: Duuude... I am, like, *totally* craving a good burger right now. Like, you have no idea.
We have a bunch of rations stored here, but it's, like, *nothing* compared to the stuff they serve at [0]Chiaroscuro Cuisine[/].
It's, like, a total shame all the *good* food's been infected with ink... it must've left the canned beans alone 'cause it hates 'em as much as I do.
Like, I even went to [0]Sanofari[/] to grab some grub, and the food looked like... literal grubs. Like, dude.
Wait, hold up. You tellin' me you ain't heard of Sanofari? Don't they teach kingdom regions in, like, negative first grade or something?
You must be a real young'un. And being the wise, mature, elderly 15- and-a-half-year-old I am, I can tell you all you'll ever need to know about the world.

Zq: Tell me more about the kingdom regions.
Vq: No thanks, I'll go to negative first grade.

a: You never tried Chiaroscuro Cuisine? Man, it was the best food in the kingdom, hands down.
Some have accused it of being simple fast food, but no, this place is *classy*. It's got, like, napkins with checkered patterns on them and everything!
The burgers are painted with the finest materials and such attention to detail, and seasoned with mouthwatering sequins and glue...
It's no wonder they had a monopoly on the entire restaurant industry for so many decades!
That is, until the CEO turned into a corrupted ink monster and devoured his shareholders.
From what I've heard, this whole ink zombification-type deal had a devastating effect on the economy.
That's right, it's tough. You don't know true cuisine until you've tried Chiaroscuro>(TM)<.
...I just quoted the restaurant slogan. Why did I do that?
Nothin' to say? Fine, I didn't wanna talk to you anyway, dude. Like, *dude*, dude. *Dude.*

OPERAND2: Tell me more about the kingdom regions.

a: So there's like, Fliptanaria, Sanofari, Inkwell, Deepenfoul, Drimoria, Woodgrove, Crossroads... Which one do you want to hear about?
So like, [0]Fliptanaria[/]'s way up north, and like... imagine being in an oven. Like, while it's on. Now imagine, like, a b'jillion times hotter than that.
Now imagine that heat, but dialed down by, I dunno, 27 percent. That's Fliptanaria. It's got volcanoes spewing molten gunk all over the place, it's insane.
It's also the part of the kingdom with the highest elevation, so you've got to do some climbing to get up there. Not somethin' I ever plan to do.
In the northeast, you've got [0]Sanofari[/], which I already talked about. It used to be this vast desert with just, like, nothing but miles of sand.
But once the best restaurant ever Chiaroscuro Cuisine came along, man, the visitors wouldn't stop comin'! Turned the place into this, like, thriving utopia or whatever.
But in the last two years, there's been a lot less visitors and the area has kinda returned to its deserted state. Nothin' much but sand and cactuses these days.
You ever been to [0]Inkwell[/] to the east? 'Course not, whole place is in ruins and the entrance has been sealed off for like a thousand years or somethin'.
It's said that it was once the kingdom's capital, so like... that's kinda weird, I guess.
To the southeast are the caverns of [0]Deepenfoul[/]. This laboratory-type building called Ballpoint Base is there.
Scientists were working on an antidote to the corruption over there, back in the day... Didn't work out well, as you can guess.
But there's also rumors of some kind of dungeon deeper below in the caverns? Like, some prison where an ancient evil is sealed or whatever.
Not that I believe that stuff. Go on down there, you probably won't find anything interesting. Probably.
In the southwest, just off the Canvas Coast, you'll find the ocean of [0]Drimoria[/]. Not much to say about the ocean, really. It's blue.
[0]Woodgrove[/] is the forest that's just to the west of us. Fortunately the corrupted ink hasn't had too bad an effect on it...
The trees are a bit sparser now, but there's still plenty of greenery to be found, making it a nice place to go for a walk...
Y'know. If it weren't for those darn ink monsters, and the weird tape lady who floats around there all the time.
This town sits on the border between Woodgrove and the [0]Crosshatched Crossroads[/].
The smallest of the regions, the Crossroads are in the center of the kingdom and connect to just about every other region, hence the name.
It's known for its mountains and unusual rock structures. Wait, what the heck am I talking about?
Am I seriously rambling about rock structures? Jeez, guess it's been a while since I've had someone to talk to. Go on, get outta here.
Oh hey, you broke the seal. I guess that makes it a lot easier to get here from the crossroads.
>But it looked really cool...
In ancient times, when corruption first began to spread, the Sages put up multiple defenses in the form of magic seals.
One separating the capital from the crossroads, and in case the first seal were to fail, a second blocking off the path to Sanofari.
Fascinating, isn't it? It draws its power from the nearby orb. Thus, breaking the orb would break the seal as well.
Though it is still unknown exactly what the runes emanating from the seal mean. We do not have the tools to translate them...
Perhaps the glyphs themselves hold some sort of mystical energy? They could be the reason the seal has lasted as long as it has.
Regardless, it sure is interesting to watch, isn't it?
It's okay, Denise, it's just me...
You're still there, I know it... you still remember me, don't you...?
Denise...? This... this isn't you. Please wake up...
Denise... I...
You look worried. But it's okay, everything will be fine!
The kingdom is all covered in gross gook right now, but soon the Destined Deity will save us! Just like how they beat the Eraser!
Maybe someday, when my mommy and daddy get back from vacation, we can all celebrate together!
My little sister has always been such an optimist. Hearing her bright outlook on these dark days... it helps me get through life.
But at the same time, it breaks my heart... I fear this will only end in disappointment for her.
I'd love nothing more than to be proven wrong. Please... whoever you are, do whatever you can to make my sister right.
What have I done?
\\It's okay, it's just me... it's just...
\\Order? What are you... talking about...?
\\What's... what's happening to you? You're...
\\The ink is corrupted, you'll... you'll...
\\No... don't go in there...
We're the Tip Twins! We explore the world giving advice to our fellow adventurers! I give advice on exploration, while my twin here tells you how to avoid danger.
^It's only 49 dollars for a tip! What do you say?
...Wait, you have no money? Well, uh... maybe we can tell you the advice now, and you can pay us later. If you want. How does that sound?
Great! First rule of exploration, stick to your guns! Metaphorically speaking. Unless you have actual guns, in which case stick to those too.
What I'm saying is, if you've got multiple paths ahead, make your choice and don't look back! Don't bother checking out what the other paths have to offer.
And if that results in a dead end, so be it. You'll just be stuck there forever.
That's horrible advice. You should find out what's at the end of every path. That way, you know which one leads to your destination.
Hey, *I'm* the exploration expert here! Next tip, think *really* hard about where to go. After all, the fate of your adventure depends on it!
That's not true. If there are multiple paths, you can go down whichever one you want, it doesn't really matter.
After all, every path leads to something good.
That's not true! Which leads to my third tip... when you can no longer progress down a path, just leave it behind.
It's just a dead end, so there's no point in ever going back there. Just forget about that area entirely.
No, you should keep that area in mind. You might acquire more abilities as you go, which will allow you to get past those areas.
What?! Then why haven't *I* found any of these abilities?
What? I give you a generous offer, and you turn it down?! Why, I oughta... I...
Tell you what, I'll lower my price by 50 percent. I'm desperate.
We're the Tip Twins! We explore the world assisting our fellow adventurers with all the tips and tricks we've acquired over the past few years!
We've only been exploring for a few days.
>Shut up, I want this person to trust our advice!
My tips are all about avoiding danger. What do you say?
Cool, cool. So, those inky guys? Avoid them at *all costs*. Even just walking past them is enough to hurt you.
That's not true. You only take damage from touching [0]red[/] things!
Oh, I see. Those ink creatures aren't red, so... does that mean they're actually harmless?
Not quite. You see, they have these attacks where they grow red spikes and stuff. *Those* attacks can hurt you.
Interesting. So you *can* walk past enemies? And they only hurt you when they're in the middle of a [0]red[/] attack?
I always just run away whenever I see one of those guys, so I didn't know that.
Now let's discuss combat! When you fight an enemy, you should stay as far away from them as possible so they don't attack you.
Now let's discuss combat! Do you have a weapon of any kind?~~~ No?~~~ That's fine, I'm sure you'll get one at some point.
Once you get a weapon, stay as far away from your opponent as possible so they don't attack you!
That's not good advice. If you have a short weapon, you'll have to stay close to your opponent to strike them.
The challenge lies in the timing. Know when to get close to an enemy, and when to back away from an attack.
How do you know when to time your attacks and dodges?
An enemy will usually give some kind of subtle warning before it attacks. You need to recognize those warnings and follow them up with a dodge.
